Poland plans to raise heating prices twice in 1997 . The Polish government ' s economic council ( KERM ) on Monday recomended to the full cabinet that household heating and hot water prices will increase twice in 1997 , a finance ministry official said . Stefan Lober from the ministry ' s national economy department said the KERM plan envisaged a 10 percent increase in heating prices in January and five percent in July 1997 . KERM ' s proposal now has to be passed by the full government to become law . Poland last increased household heating and hot water prices by about five percent on October 1 , 1996 . - - Warsaw Newsroom + 48 22 653 9700 
